DOC-008
Enterprise Data Model (Physical + Logical Schema)
1. Amaç

Bu belge:

MARS sistemindeki tüm verilerin gerçek relational database (PostgreSQL) yapısını tanımlar.

Bu model:

ORM’e birebir çevrilebilir
migration üretilebilir
OR-Tools input oluşturabilir
AI feature store’a kaynak olur
2. Tasarım Prensipleri
2.1 Tek Doğruluk Kaynağı
Operasyonel veri → PostgreSQL
Event → Kafka (append-only)
Analitik → ayrı store
2.2 Multi-layer model
Master Data
→ Production Data
→ Execution Data
→ Decision Data
→ AI Data
→ Event Data
2.3 Tenant Model

Her tablo:

factory_id UUID

zorunlu içerir.

3. MASTER DATA SCHEMA
3.1 Factory
Factory (
  id UUID PK,
  name TEXT,
  location TEXT,
  shift_model_id UUID,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)
3.2 ProductionLine
ProductionLine (
  id UUID PK,
  factory_id UUID FK,
  name TEXT,
  type TEXT,
  capacity INT,
  wip_limit INT
)
3.3 WorkCenter
WorkCenter (
  id UUID PK,
  line_id UUID FK,
  name TEXT,
  bottleneck_flag BOOLEAN
)
3.4 Machine
Machine (
  id UUID PK,
  workcenter_id UUID FK,
  type TEXT,
  status TEXT,
  oee FLOAT,
  max_speed FLOAT
)
3.5 Operator
Operator (
  id UUID PK,
  factory_id UUID FK,
  name TEXT,
  shift_id UUID,
  efficiency FLOAT,
  status TEXT
)
3.6 Skill
Skill (
  id UUID PK,
  name TEXT,
  category TEXT
)
3.7 OperatorSkill
OperatorSkill (
  operator_id UUID FK,
  skill_id UUID FK,
  level INT,
  speed_factor FLOAT,
  quality_factor FLOAT
)
3.8 Product
Product (
  id UUID PK,
  code TEXT,
  name TEXT,
  customer_id UUID
)
3.9 Operation
Operation (
  id UUID PK,
  product_id UUID FK,
  name TEXT,
  sequence INT,
  smv FLOAT,
  machine_type TEXT,
  skill_required INT
)
4. PRODUCTION DATA SCHEMA
4.1 Order
Order (
  id UUID PK,
  factory_id UUID,
  customer_id UUID,
  priority INT,
  due_date TIMESTAMP,
  status TEXT
)
4.2 OrderItem
OrderItem (
  id UUID PK,
  order_id UUID FK,
  product_id UUID FK,
  quantity INT
)
4.3 FlowUnit
FlowUnit (
  id UUID PK,
  order_item_id UUID FK,
  current_operation_id UUID,
  status TEXT,
  priority INT,
  split_group_id UUID
)
4.4 OperationInstance
OperationInstance (
  id UUID PK,
  flow_unit_id UUID FK,
  operation_id UUID FK,
  status TEXT,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP,
  assigned_operator_id UUID,
  assigned_machine_id UUID
)
4.5 Queue
Queue (
  id UUID PK,
  workcenter_id UUID FK,
  flow_unit_id UUID FK,
  position INT
)
5. EXECUTION DATA
5.1 Assignment
Assignment (
  id UUID PK,
  operator_id UUID,
  operation_instance_id UUID,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP
)
5.2 ProductionEvent
ProductionEvent (
  id UUID PK,
  type TEXT,
  entity_id UUID,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  payload JSONB
)
5.3 Decision
Decision (
  id UUID PK,
  decision_type TEXT,
  factory_id UUID,
  state_hash TEXT,
  input_snapshot JSONB,
  output_snapshot JSONB,
  score FLOAT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)
6. SKILL & PERFORMANCE MODEL
6.1 OperatorPerformance
OperatorPerformance (
  id UUID PK,
  operator_id UUID,
  operation_id UUID,
  avg_cycle_time FLOAT,
  defect_rate FLOAT,
  fatigue_index FLOAT,
  learning_rate FLOAT
)
6.2 LearningCurve
LearningCurve (
  id UUID PK,
  operator_id UUID,
  operation_id UUID,
  iteration INT,
  cycle_time FLOAT
)
7. AI / FEATURE STORE
7.1 FeatureSnapshot
FeatureSnapshot (
  id UUID PK,
  entity_type TEXT,
  entity_id UUID,
  features JSONB,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)
7.2 PredictionLog
PredictionLog (
  id UUID PK,
  model_name TEXT,
  input JSONB,
  output JSONB,
  confidence FLOAT
)
8. INDEX STRATEJİSİ
Kritik indexler
flow_unit_id
operation_instance_id
operator_id
machine_id
factory_id
timestamp
Composite Index
(factory_id, status)
(workcenter_id, position)
(flow_unit_id, current_operation_id)
9. EVENT INTEGRATION

Her tablo event ile sync olur:

DB Write
→ Event Produced
→ Kafka
→ State Update
→ Analytics
10. DATA RELATIONSHIP CORE
Order
  → OrderItem
      → FlowUnit
          → OperationInstance
              → Assignment
                  → Operator
                  → Machine
11. BU BELGENİN KRİTİK NOKTASI

Bu model olmadan:

OR-Tools input üretilemez
AI feature store çalışmaz
real-time decision mümkün olmaz
